\section{Test Observations}
\label{sec:obs}
The H{\sc{ii}} region Ori\,A and Galactic centre source Sgr\,A were the targets for our test observations (Table~\ref{tab:regionInfo}).
Observations were conducted under Tid-70m project T206, as part of the OTF development programme.
Our test observations used the 8.2--8.6~GHz X-band receiver and recorded both circular polarisations with 64~MHz bandwidth, sampling at a quarter FWHM with the minimum three second intervals.
The beam has FWHM 1.8\arcmin, and individual scans (map rows) were spaced by 30\arcsec\ in Dec, while the telescope scanned along the $\alpha\cdot\cos\,\delta_{0}$ axis.
A schedule file parameter set the time taken for the telescope to complete each scan: 
These observations used 120s-long scans with 30s integrations on the reference position.
The Hanning function was not applied for the maps presented, as RRLs are broad spectral features, so Hanning is not required.
Opacity correction was not applied to our maps, but attenuation due to opacity would be within 5\% at the lowest elevation during the 8\,GHz observations.
There was no comparison to a flux calibrator source, but our observations agree within 10\% with those of \cite{Cesarsky}.

